<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Habitat and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Scattered on soil in tropical forests dominated by 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Castanopsis" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Castanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Coniferophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
). Currently known from southern and south-western China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. H. Li, W. Q. Deng &amp; B. Song, Fungal Diversity 12: 123" authorityYear="2013" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="Gyroporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gyroporus brunneofloccosus" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brunneofloccosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Gyroporus brunneofloccosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, originally described from southern China, is characterised by the initially dark brown to brown and then brown to light red-brown pileus with concolorous floccose-scaly to coarsely tomentose squamules, the extended pileal margin, the white pileal context staining cerulean blue or greenish-blue to dark blue or deep blue when bruised, the initially yellowish to pale yellow and then greenish-yellow hymenophore staining cerulean blue to greenish-blue when bruised, the brownish to brown or light red-brown stipe, the spongy and then hollow context in the stipe, the frequent clamp connections in all tissues, the ellipsoid basidiospores and the distribution in tropical forests dominated by plants of the families 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fagaceae" genus="Gyroporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pinaceae" genus="Gyroporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Li, TH" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="123 - 127" publicationUrl="https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Li, TH, Deng, WQ, Song, B, 2003. A new cyanescent species of Gyroporus from China. Fungal Diversity 12: 123 - 127, https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" title="A new cyanescent species of Gyroporus from China." url="https://www.fungaldiversity.org/fdp/sfdp/FD12-123-127.pdf" volume="12" year="2003">Li et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
In China, 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. brunneofloccosus" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brunneofloccosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. brunneofloccosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was misidentified as 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. cyanescens" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cyanescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. cyanescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Bi et al. (1990, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bi, ZS" journalOrPublisher="Guangdong Science and Technology, Guangdong" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" publicationUrl="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/bf3d5f8d7bd973ed.html" refId="B3" refString="Bi, ZS, Zheng, GY, Li, TH, 1994. Macrofungus Flora of Guangdong Province. Guangdong Science and Technology, Guangdong, https://book.ixueshu.com/book/bf3d5f8d7bd973ed.html" title="Macrofungus Flora of Guangdong Province." url="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/bf3d5f8d7bd973ed.html" year="1994">1994</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Ying, JZ" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" publicationUrl="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/a3f03cd59a016ac3.html" refId="B37" refString="Ying, JZ, Zang, M, 1994. Economic Macrofungi from South-western China. Science Press, Beijing, https://book.ixueshu.com/book/a3f03cd59a016ac3.html" title="Economic Macrofungi from South-western China." url="https://book.ixueshu.com/book/a3f03cd59a016ac3.html" year="1994">Ying and Zang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mao, XL" journalOrPublisher="Henan Science and Technology Press, Zhengzhou" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" publicationUrl="https://book.douban.com/subject/1433850/" refId="B25" refString="Mao, XL, 2000. The Macrofungi in China. Henan Science and Technology Press, Zhengzhou, https://book.douban.com/subject/1433850/" title="The Macrofungi in China." url="https://book.douban.com/subject/1433850/" year="2000">Mao (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. However, these two species can be separated both by phylogenetic and morphological evidence. Our phylogenetic analysis of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">atp6</emphasis>
data (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum Likelihood phylogenetic tree of Gyroporus inferred from the atp 6 dataset. Bootstrap frequencies (&gt; 50 %) are shown above or below supported branches. Newly-sequenced collections are indicated in bold. Species vouchers and countries of origin are provided after the species name successively." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.81.65660.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/570653" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">1</figureCitation>
) indicates that 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Gyroporaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. brunneofloccosus" order="Boletales" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="brunneofloccosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">G. brunneofloccosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
